That smells nice.

01:54.882 --> 01:57.382
It's lavender.
I got the organic.

01:57.384 --> 01:58.684
No preservatives...

01:58.686 --> 02:01.787
Unlike melton's turtle.

02:03.156 --> 02:05.657
Had to be there.

02:05.659 --> 02:07.292
I just love these.

02:07.294 --> 02:10.395
I used to have a pair
just like them.

02:10.396 --> 02:11.797
Is that garnet hill?

02:11.799 --> 02:13.799
Um, saddle bridge.

02:13.801 --> 02:16.401
It's cute.
Why'd you stop wearing them?

02:16.403 --> 02:18.537
Guess I didn't want
to stand out.

02:18.539 --> 02:20.539
In a pair of clogs?

02:20.541 --> 02:23.375
In anything, really.

02:28.215 --> 02:29.615
I'm gonna pretend

02:29.617 --> 02:31.683
You're not in here
past visiting hours again.

02:31.685 --> 02:34.253
Sweet marla, my co-conspirator.

02:34.255 --> 02:36.855
I'll check back in a bit.

02:36.857 --> 02:38.590
Everybody's been so nice here.

02:38.592 --> 02:40.526
It's because we're not
in paulie, mother.

02:40.528 --> 02:42.561
You'll notice a difference
in tone sometimes

02:42.563 --> 02:44.363
When people don't wish
you were dead.

02:44.365 --> 02:46.298
That's pleasant.

02:46.300 --> 02:47.533
Just saying.

02:49.269 --> 02:50.636
I better get on the road, then.

02:50.638 --> 02:53.205
Thank you for keeping watch,
amantha.

02:53.207 --> 02:54.773
I know the drive is a bear.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.708
It's what we do.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.477
I am my brother's keeper.

02:58.479 --> 03:00.412
It won't be forever, honey.

03:00.414 --> 03:02.714
Then what will I do?
Get a job?

03:02.716 --> 03:05.517
I can't even think
about a job right now.

03:05.519 --> 03:07.786
Gonna have to sooner or later.

03:07.788 --> 03:08.820
How about later?

03:10.925 --> 03:12.324
Mama, don't forget your catalog.

03:18.898 --> 03:21.400
He's not a china doll.

03:21.402 --> 03:22.634
What?

03:22.636 --> 03:24.570
You're not gonna break him.

03:27.240 --> 03:29.408
God, mama.

03:29.410 --> 03:31.910
What are we gonna do?

03:31.912 --> 03:34.246
What we've been doing.

03:34.248 --> 03:37.449
Stay positive.
Keep hoping.

03:37.451 --> 03:39.418
Keep hoping.

03:41.922 --> 03:43.889
Good night, my sweethearts.

04:31.037 --> 04:33.472
I'm telling you, dad,
we're gonna drag ass on this,

04:33.474 --> 04:36.008
And we're gonna miss the best
opportunity we've had in years.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.342
Wheel rims.

04:37.344 --> 04:38.577
Specialization, dad.

04:38.579 --> 04:40.445
It's where retail's going.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.748
And we got to get out
in front of it.

04:42.750 --> 04:44.650
Where'd you get that idea?

04:44.652 --> 04:46.652
I've been working on it
for a while now.

04:46.654 --> 04:49.321
It's all they could talk about
at the tire conference.

04:49.323 --> 04:52.991
We sell tires, son.
Sell... not rent.

04:52.993 --> 04:56.495
People today...
they want flash, you know?

04:56.497 --> 04:58.463
They... they...
they want bling.

04:58.465 --> 04:59.731
They want stuff they can afford.

04:59.733 --> 05:01.400
Fair enough, okay?

05:01.402 --> 05:03.335
But they can afford to rent
high-quality wheel rims

05:03.337 --> 05:04.770
At an affordable weekly fee.

05:04.772 --> 05:06.905
And they'll rent them
by the truckloads.

05:06.907 --> 05:08.674
That's all that matters to me.

05:08.676 --> 05:09.875
Hmm.

05:12.679 --> 05:14.980
Dad, the numbers don't lie.

05:14.982 --> 05:18.917
Three straight months
of declining sales.

05:18.919 --> 05:20.886
Hey, whoa, whoa. We got
to microwave this thing.

05:20.888 --> 05:22.487
We ain't got time
for an oven bake.

05:22.489 --> 05:24.356
The microwave makes it mushy.

05:24.358 --> 05:26.591
Yeah, I know.
It's got the, uh, little
reflectors built into it.

05:26.593 --> 05:27.826
It gives it
that oven-baked flavor.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.428
Just make the salad.

05:33.634 --> 05:36.101
Listen.

05:36.103 --> 05:37.803
I know a lot of things are up
in the air right now.

05:37.805 --> 05:39.404
A lot of things?

05:39.406 --> 05:41.506
We need a new revenue stream,
and we need it quick.

05:41.508 --> 05:43.709
And this is it.

05:43.711 --> 05:45.610
Where's the cheese and tomatoes?

05:45.612 --> 05:46.978
What's it cost?

05:48.815 --> 05:51.450
Well, you got to spend money
to make money.

05:51.452 --> 05:52.951
What's the investment, ted?

05:52.953 --> 05:55.554
I'm still working
on the final numbers...

05:55.556 --> 05:59.658
But no more than 40k, 50k, tops.

05:59.660 --> 06:00.959
$50,000?

06:00.961 --> 06:02.894
Tops, dad.

06:02.896 --> 06:05.831
Where's the spatula?

06:05.833 --> 06:08.233
I don't know.
Use that cake thing.

06:11.771 --> 06:14.211
You got to trust me
on this, dad.

06:14.907 --> 06:19.444
I don't see it, son.
Not right now.

06:27.620 --> 06:30.555
Well... There's something else
we ain't talked about

06:30.557 --> 06:33.037
That ain't nobody
wanted to talk about.

06:34.527 --> 06:36.161
What if daniel wakes up
out of this coma,

06:36.163 --> 06:38.096
And he's a damn
veggie burger?
Easy, ted.

06:38.098 --> 06:39.765
I ain't trying to be crass, dad,

06:39.767 --> 06:41.600
But what if mom's
got to wipe his ass

06:41.602 --> 06:42.634
For the next 20 years?

06:42.636 --> 06:44.102
What are y'all arguing about?

06:46.105 --> 06:49.608
We're just having
a conversation, son.

06:49.610 --> 06:53.044
I'll be in my room.

